para.p:
Language modeling research in low-resource languages often relies on large multilingual models trained on many languages simultaneously (
            , 
          ).
For many low-resource languages, a dedicated model optimized for that language does not exist.
This lack of dedicated models hinders comparability of results across models and languages (
            , 
          ), and it contributes to model under-performance in low-resource languages (
            , 
          ).
These barriers to research in low-resource languages are likely to exacerbate existing inequities across language communities in NLP research (
            , 
          ).

